data.title: Recent Mercedes spot - Spectrasonics Bob Moog library
data.meta_description: I did this job the day I picked up the Tribute to Bob Moog Omnisphere library, and made a point to write the track attempting to use almost entirely the...
data.text:
Yep just went to air.

And in all honesty I didn't do a ton of processing besides eq and compression, a smidge of simple things like delays and verbs, and perhaps some creative audio slicing here and there. That's the beauty of this library, the presets are really fantastic and useable on a wide scale. Expertly programmed stuff to begin with...not a lot of need to futz, and the programmed controls do great things to the sounds to keep them dynamic.

I've never really been a dial up the presets guy but this library felt like it needed a get to know you project as the sounds have a simple but cutting edge quality about them, something that lacks from most preset sets (always overdone I feel like).

Daniel I dunno but probably if you recognize it!! Awesome work if you were responsible for some of the sounds! Thank you and thanks for your contribution!!

Great work again mate.

Dan
